{"questionId":"11824","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>This question will investigate the solution to a coupled system of differential equations and how to transform it to a system that can be solved by the eigenvector method.</p>\n<p>It is desired to solve the coupled system of differential equations</p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot x = x + 2y - 50\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>x</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>50</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"\\dot y = 2x + y - 40\">\n  <mrow>\n    <mover>\n      <mi>y</mi>\n      <mo>˙</mo>\n    </mover>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>2</mn>\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mo>+</mo>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mo>−</mo>\n  <mn>40</mn>\n</math></span></p>\n<p>where <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;represent the population of two types of symbiotic coral and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;is time measured in decades.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Hence find the exact values of <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n</math></span> and <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y\">\n  <mi>y</mi>\n</math></span>&nbsp;when <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"t = 1\">\n  <mi>t</mi>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1</mn>\n</math></span>, giving the answers to 4 significant figures.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\\left( 1 \\right) = 1226{\\text{,}}\\,\\,y\\left( 1 \\right) = 1214\\,\\,\\left( {4sf} \\right)\">\n  <mi>x</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1226</mn>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>,</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mi>y</mi>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mn>1</mn>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n  <mn>1214</mn>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n  <mrow>\n    <mo>(</mo>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>4</mn>\n      <mi>s</mi>\n      <mi>f</mi>\n    </mrow>\n    <mo>)</mo>\n  </mrow>\n</math></span>&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"11824","referenceCode":"EXM.3.AHL.TZ0.3g","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Hence find the exact values of x and y when t = 1 , giving the answers to 4 significant figures.","paper":"3","level":"HL","questionNumber":"g","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 5—Calculus","Topic 5—Calculus","AHL 5.17—Phase portrait"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}